@node eplay "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "MixTiles" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher and a Workbench with at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  The game board consists of an area of 7 by 7 piles of coloured
tiles. Each pile contains 4 tiles of one of the following colours:
red, blue, green and yellow which are randomly stacked. None of the
tiles that are located on top of each pile are of the same colour
as those that are on top of neighbouring piles. Tiles that are
located under are visible by their borders.

  Gameplay is done by clicking on a tile, if neighbouring tiles,
either horizontally and/or vertically, are of the same colour to
the one that has been clicked, the tiles will 'explode' and will be
removed. Note that only the uppermost tiles in each pile can be
associated to tiles of the same colour, those that are located
under remain inactive. You get points according to the number of
eliminated tiles: 2 tiles give 1 point, 3 tiles give 4 points,
4 tiles give 8 points and 5 tiles give 16 points.

  If there are no neighbouring tiles of the same colour, the
clicked tile will be moved under its pile of tiles. If that tile is
the only one at that position, it will remain as is.

  The game continues as long as there are neighbouring tiles of the
same colour. It makes no difference where the tiles are located in
the piles. However, avoid isolating tiles, if that happens, when no
neighbouring tiles of the same colour will remain, the game will be
over... 

  If you sucessfully remove all tiles on the game board, MixTiles
will display a new board to play with...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

